erals top level Biographical Information Early Life Raleigh Edward Colston  b  Paris  France on October 31  1825  Adopted son of Dr  Raleigh Edward Colston  1796 1881  and his wife Maria Theresa  Duchess of Valmey  ca  1775 1845  The young Colston was sent to the United States in 1842  in care of his uncle Edward Colston of Berkeley Co   West  Virginia  to complete his education  VMI record Entered VMI on July 8  1843  was graduated on July 4  1846  standing 4th in a class of 14  Marriage Louise Meriwether Bowyer of  Thorn Hill  Rockbridge Co  Virginia  Two daughters  Mary Frances and Louise Elizabeth  Pre Civil War Professor of French at VMI from 1846 until outbreak of war  In November 1859  he accompanied a contigent of VMI cadets assigned to guard duty at the execution of abolitionist John Brown  Civil War Commissioned Col  16th Virginia Infantry Regiment  1862 Dec  appointed Brigadier General and led brigade under Longstreet in the Peninsula  given brigade under Jackson in April 1863 and commanded a division at Chancellorsville  served under Beauregard in defense of Petersburg in 1864  in command at Lynchburg at end of war  Post war Established military school in North Carolina Colonel Egyptian army  1873 1879  War Dept  clerk  1882 1894  died 1896  at Soldiers  Home  Richmond  VA  buried Hollywood Cemetery  Richmond    Related collection in VMI Archives Raleigh E  Colston Papers Archives   Civil War Resources   Generals   Raleigh E  Colston Biography Archives   Civil War Resources   Generals   Raleigh E  Colston Biography Archives Civil War Resources Generals Raleigh E  Colston Biography     VMI s Civil War Generals Raleigh E  Colston  Class of 1846 VMI Civil War Generals top level Biographical Information Early Life Raleigh Edward Colston  b  Paris  France on October 31  1825  Adopted son of Dr  Raleigh Edward Colston  1796 1881  and his wife Maria Theresa  Duchess of Valmey  ca  1775 1845  The young Colston was sent to the United States in 1842  in care of his uncle Edward Colston of Berkeley Co   West  Virginia  to complete his education  VMI record Entered VMI on July 8  1843  was graduated on July 4  1846  standing 4th in a class of 14  Marriage Louise Meriwether Bowyer of  Thorn Hill  Rockbridge Co  Virginia  Two daughters  Mary Frances and Louise Elizabeth  Pre Civil War Professor of French at VMI from 1846 until outbreak of war  In November 1859  he accompanied a contigent of VMI cadets assigned to guard duty at the execution of abolitionist John Brown  Civil War Commissioned Col  16th Virginia Infantry Regiment  1862 Dec  appointed Brigadier General and led brigade under Longstreet in the Peninsula  given brigade under Jackson in April 1863 and commanded a division at Chancellorsville  served under Beauregard in defense of Petersburg in 1864  in command at Lynchburg at end of war  Post war Established military school in North Carolina Colonel Egyptian army  1873 1879  War Dept  clerk  1882 1894  died 1896  at Soldiers  Home  Richmond  VA  buried Hollywood Cemetery  Richmond    Related collection in VMI Archives Raleigh E  Colston Papers VMI s Civil War Generals Raleigh E  Colston  Class of 1846  VMI Civil War Generals top level VMI Civil War Generals top level Biographical Information Early Life Raleigh Edward Colston  b  Paris  France on October 31  1825  Adopted son of Dr  Raleigh Edward Colston  1796 1881  and his wife Maria Theresa  Duchess of Valmey  ca  1775 1845  The young Colston was sent to the United States in 1842  in care of his uncle Edward Colston of Berkeley Co   West  Virginia  to complete his education  VMI record Entered VMI on July 8  1843  was graduated on July 4  1846  standing 4th in a class of 14  Marriage Louise Meriwether Bowyer of  Thorn Hill  Rockbridge Co  Virginia  Two daughters  Mary Frances and Louise Elizabeth  Pre Civil War Professor of French at VMI from 1846 until outbreak of war  In November 1859  he accompanied a contigent of VMI cadets assigned to guard duty at the execution of abolitionist John Brown  Civil War Commissioned Col  16th Virginia Infantry Regiment  1862 Dec  appointed Brigadier General and led brigade under Longstreet in the Peninsula  given brigade under Jackson in April 1863 and commanded a division at Chancellorsville  served under Beauregard in defense of Petersburg in 1864  in command at Lynchburg at end of war  Post war Established military school in North Carolina Colonel Egyptian army  1873 1879  War Dept  clerk  1882 1894  died 1896  at Soldiers  Home  Richmond  VA  buried Hollywood Cemetery  Richmond    Related collection in VMI Archives Raleigh E  Colston Papers Biographical Information Early Life Raleigh Edward Colston  b  Paris  France on October 31  1825  Adopted son of Dr  Raleigh Edward Colston  1796 1881  and his wife Maria Theresa  Duchess of Valmey  ca  1775 1845  The young Colston was sent to the United States in 1842  in care of his uncle Edward Colston of Berkeley Co   West  Virginia  to complete his education  VMI record Entered VMI on July 8  1843  was graduated on July 4  1846  standing 4th in a class of 14  Marriage Louise Meriwether Bowyer of  Thorn Hill  Rockbridge Co  Virginia  Two daughters  Mary Frances and Louise Elizabeth  Pre Civil War Professor of French at VMI from 1846 until outbreak of war  In November 1859  he accompanied a contigent of VMI cadets assigned to guard duty at the execution of abolitionist John Brown  Civil War Commissioned Col  16th Virginia Infantry Regiment  1862 Dec  appointed Brigadier General and led brigade under Longstreet in the Peninsula  given brigade under Jackson in April 1863 and commanded a division at Chancellorsville  served under Beauregard in defense of Petersburg in 1864  in command at Lynchburg at end of war  Post war Established military school in North Carolina Colonel Egyptian army  1873 1879  War Dept  clerk  1882 1894  died 1896  at Soldiers  Home  Richmond  VA  buried Hollywood Cemetery  Richmond Biographical Information   Early Life Raleigh Edward Colston  b  Paris  France on October 31  1825  Adopted son of Dr  Raleigh Edward Colston  1796 1881  and his wife Maria Theresa  Duchess of Valmey  ca  1775 1845  The young Colston was sent to the United States in 1842  in care of his uncle Edward Colston of Berkeley Co   West  Virginia  to complete his education  VMI record Entered VMI on July 8  1843  was graduated on July 4  1846  standing 4th in a class of 14  Marriage Louise Meriwether Bowyer of  Thorn Hill  Rockbridge Co  Virginia  Two daughters  Mary Frances and Louise Elizabeth  Pre Civil War Professor of French at VMI from 1846 until outbreak of war  In November 1859  he accompanied a contigent of VMI cadets assigned to guard duty at the execution of abolitionist John Brown  Civil War Commissioned Col  16th Virginia Infantry Regiment  1862 Dec  appointed Brigadier General and led brigade under Longstreet in the Peninsula  given brigade under Jackson in April 1863 and commanded a division at Chancellorsville  served under Beauregard in defense of Petersburg in 1864  in command at Lynchburg at end of war  Post war Established military school in North Carolina Colonel Egyptian army  1873 1879  War Dept  clerk  1882 1894  died 1896  at Soldiers  Home  Richmond  VA  buried Hollywood Cemetery  Richmond Early Life Raleigh Edward Colston  b  Paris  France on October 31  1825  Adopted son of Dr  Raleigh Edward Colston  1796 1881  and his wife Maria Theresa  Duchess of Valmey  ca  1775 1845  The young Colston was sent to the United States in 1842  in care of his uncle Edward Colston of Berkeley Co   West  Virginia  to complete his education Early Life  VMI record Entered VMI on July 8  1843  was graduated on July 4  1846  standing 4th in a class of 14 VMI record  Marriage Louise Meriwether Bowyer of  Thorn Hill  Rockbridge Co  Virginia  Two daughters  Mary Frances and Louise Elizabeth Marriage  Pre Civil War Professor of French at VMI from 1846 until outbreak of war  In November 1859  he accompanied a contigent o